+-- ── (b′) dispatch-into-single-target TMC context (TRMC-DESIGN dispatch group) ─
+-- The LLVM analogue of the WASM (b′) emit (WASMGC-TRMC-DESIGN.md §11).  WASM
+-- threaded the destination through 3 MODULE GLOBALS + cross-function `return_call`;
+-- LLVM can't `br` across a define boundary, so the hot loop is the `musttail call`
+-- cycle through the group's INNER symbols (the proven cross-fn-musttail analogue of
+-- return_call — same as the float wrapper→worker split), and the destination lives
+-- in 3 module globals: `@g_tmc_head` (i64, the list head), `@g_tmc_dest` (ptr, the
+-- next tail word to fill), `@g_tmc_first` (i64, 1 until the first cell is built).
+--
+-- THE LLVM-SPECIFIC CONSTRAINT (the one thing WASM got for free): `musttail`
+-- requires the caller and callee PROTOTYPES to match exactly.  A (b′) group's
+-- members have HETEROGENEOUS arities — a router `scanAt` carries an extra dispatch
+-- param vs the root `scan` it spine-conses to — so a member define of arity N
+-- cannot `musttail` an inner loop of arity R≠N.  WASM's `return_call` threads any
+-- args, so there it was free.  The fix: every group member emits TWO defines — a
+-- PUBLIC `@mdk_<m>(real arity)` for external callers (a plain `call` into the inner
+-- symbol — rare, not in the hot loop, ABI-preserving) and an INNER
+-- `@mdk_<m>__disp(UNIFORM arity U)` that the hot musttail cycle stays within (U =
+-- the group's max member arity; each member's real args occupy the first slots, the
+-- rest padded with 0).  All inner symbols share arity U ⇒ every hot musttail
+-- prototype-matches.  This is the price LLVM pays for not having return_call; it is
+-- contained entirely to this emit (no inliner, no whole-program caller analysis).
+--
+-- `WDispOn root rootArity uniformArity`: `root` = the group root (the spine/bare-call
+-- redirect tests); `rootArity` = the ROOT's arity (NOT the emitting member's — a
+-- router is a different arity than the root it spine-conses to; carrying the member
+-- arity here mis-redirects and drops the first token, the WASM §11 bring-up bug);
+-- `uniformArity` = U, the shared inner-symbol arity every hot musttail pads to.
+data WDispCtx = WDispOff | WDispOn String Int Int
+
+wDispCtxRef : Ref WDispCtx
+wDispCtxRef = Ref WDispOff
+
+-- the detected (b′) groups for this program, computed once in emitProgram and
+-- consulted by emitFn.  Empty when no group qualifies (then everything keeps its
+-- current codegen — Phase-1/2 self/dispatch TMC + ordinary path, NO regression).
+wDispGroupsRef : Ref (List DispGroup)
+wDispGroupsRef = Ref []
+
+-- set when ≥1 (b′) group is emitted (gates the dest-globals decl).
+wDispUsedRef : Ref Bool
+wDispUsedRef = Ref False
+
+-- the inner (uniform-arity) symbol for a member `m`: `mdk_<m>__disp`.
+wDispInner : String -> String
+wDispInner m = "mdk_" ++ m ++ "__disp"
